-- Kenya's TPS, Serena Chain Owner, Gets Regulatory Approval For Bonus Shares
-- Eric Ombok
-- 2010-06-22T04:50:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-22/kenya-s-tps-serena-chain-owner-gets-regulatory-approval-for-bonus-shares.html

          
          
             TPS Eastern Africa Ltd., the Kenyan
holding company for the Serena hotel chain, received regulatory
approval to issue holders one ordinary share for every six held.  
 “The register of members of the company will be closed on
June 24 at 5:00p.m. for the purpose of determining the bonus
entitlement for each shareholder of the company,” it said in a
statement in the Nairobi-based Daily Nation.  
